  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nBy default, the swarm HTTP API should be exposed to localhost only. Default: `http://localhost:8500`\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nActually it seems as if the swarm daemon answers any requests coming in on port 8500 such as `http://192.168.1.2:8500`\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSuggested actions:\r\n\r\n1. Immediately change swarm to listen on localhost only\r\n2. In future possibly add support for a `--listen` cli flag allowing users to specify which IPs to listen on.",
